methods.applyTo:
Apply this rollup definition to the specified table.

:param table: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) - the table to apply to
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.table.Table) a rollup, as defined by this object.
methods.equals:
Check equality with another definition. The name is not included in the equality check.

:param o: (java.lang.Object) - the other object
:return: (boolean) true if the two definitions describe the same rollup
methods.getAggregations:
Get the aggregations and applicable columns for this definition.

:return: (java.util.List<? extends io.deephaven.api.agg.Aggregation>) an unmodifiable map of aggregations to set of columns
methods.getGroupByColumns:
Get the group-by columns for this definition.

:return: (java.util.List<java.lang.String>) an unmodifiable list of group-by columns
methods.getName:
Get the name of the rollup.

:return: (java.lang.String) the name
methods.getResultMatchPairs:
Get the resulting input/output pairs as match pairs.

:return: (java.util.List<io.deephaven.engine.table.MatchPair>) The resulting match pairs
methods.includeConstituents:
Check if this definition produces a rollup with constituent columns.

:return: (boolean) true if this definition produces rollup constituents
methods.includeDescriptions:
Check if this definition produces a rollup that includes column descriptions for each aggregation.

:return: (boolean) true if column descriptions are included.
methods.includeOriginalColumns:
Check if this definition produces a rollup that includes all original columns

:return: (boolean) true if this definition includes original columns.
methods.setName:
Set the name of this rollup.

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the name

text:
This class defines a rollup. It defines both the group-by columns, their order, and all aggregations to be performed
 on other columns.
